shared_text:
Westwood Free Public Library
April 7 at 4:22 PM ·

Did you know it's National Poetry Month? Please join me in our Poetry Out Loud Challenge! Post your own video, either on Facebook or Instagram, use the hashtag #PoetryOutLoudChallenge, and be sure to mention or tag the Westwood Free Public Library so we can share your post.

When I was young, I was given a book of poems by A.A. Milne called When We Were Very Young. I loved this book and there was one poem in particular that I drove my family crazy with by parading around and reciting. What was it about this poem, I wonder, that made it stick with me all these years? For this challenge, please recite your own favorite poem out loud (it doesn't have to be perfect, as you can see!) and share the video with us to help celebrate National Poetry Month and spread some literary joy. Everyone who participates will get a prize when the library is open to the public again, which we hope will be soon!

P.S. The audiobook version of the book is available on HOOPLA, which can be accessed on our website.
#westwoodpubliclibrary #poetrysavesyoursoul

The Westwood Regional School District will open online Kindergarten pre-registration for the 2019‑2020 school year on Monday, December 3, 2019. This is a pre-registration only; students will not be considered enrolled until parents/guardians submit the required documentation at in-person registration in January 2019.

Be aware that your child must reside in the Borough of Westwood or Township of Washington and be five (5) years old on or before October 1, 2019 to enter Kindergarten next September.

For more information, click https://sites.google.com/wwrsd.org/enrollment/2019-2020-kindergarten-registration.

Westwood Regional Schools is proud to announce this year's Family Wellness program lineup.

The first event, Finding Balance, will take place on December 5 and will explore ways we can better understand the causes of stress and anxiety so that we may be able to find better balance in school, at home and in life.

All events are open to students and their families from our entire school community. Please check out the flyer for additional details and register at http://bit.ly/wrsdwellness if you'd like to attend.

post_text:
Due to the consecutive days of extreme heat, there will be an early dismissal on Thursday, September 6 for students who attend a Westwood Regional School*.
Please note, if your child attends an out of district educational facility, there is no change in schedule.

WRSD SCHEDULES
Pre-School will be dismissed at 12:05 p.m.
Grades K-5 will be dismissed at 12:45 p.m.
Middle School will be dismissed at 12:36 p.m.
All Jr./Sr. High School students will be dismissed at 12:16 p.m.
NOTE: Lunch will not be served in any building

AFTERCARE
Champions will provide extended day care upon dismissal.

JR/SR HIGH SCHOOL
Advisors/coaches will send a separate communication regarding the confirmation of schedule changes for clubs, activities, and athletics.
